cs.CR, cs.NI, cs.CY, cs.SI, cs.MM

This paper deals with the analysis of Internet censorship in Syria, which falls under the category of computer security (cs.CR). The paper also involves network infrastructure (cs.NI) and cybercrime (cs.CY) as it deals with the use of proxies, VPNs, and BitTorrent to evade censorship. The paper also involves social media (cs.SI) as it discusses the limited filtering of specific pages. Finally, the paper involves multimedia (cs.MM) as it discusses the filtering of Instant Messaging.
